e playing other games, 90% are playing EQ at any given time. That works most of the time, saves having to add them all up.<br><br>Currently there's 91746 people logged into the station. Take away 10,000 (we'll make the math easy :-) ) and you still have over 80k playing EQ at about 11pm PST.<br><br>That doesn't show much (or any) decline in EQ's population.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rexfelix>Rexfelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/5/02 12:14:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=201.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cooldude.gif" align=absmiddle>  EQ decline</span><hr size=1> Actually Molly I remember the numbers being over 140k about 6 months ago.  Furthermore, &quot;decline&quot; doesn't necessarily mean a large exodus of players.  In business, decline is often synonomous with decrease or cessation of growth.  It is possible for an industry/business to experience a decline but still remain viable/profitable.  <br><br>Rexfelix <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umollycat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mollycat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/5/02 12:56:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=201.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cooldude.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: EQ decline</span><hr size=1>